PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions about Ethereum Transaction Analysis
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Ethereum Transaction Analysis allows you to monitor and analyze new transactions happening on the Ethereum blockchain in real-time. It provides insights into transaction details like sender, receiver, amount transferred, gas fees paid, and more.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: Our app connects to Ethereum nodes and listens for new block confirmations. When a new block is mined, we parse all the transactions in that block and extract relevant details for analysis. The analyzed data is then presented through a user-friendly interface.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What kind of analysis can I do?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: You can view detailed information about each transaction, track transaction flows between addresses, identify large or suspicious transactions, monitor activity of specific addresses or contracts, and gain insights through data visualizations.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Is my data secure and private?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: Absolutely. We do not store or share any personal or identifying information from the Ethereum blockchain. All analysis happens locally on your device, ensuring your privacy and data security.
CTA_BODY: Monitor and gain valuable insights into new Ethereum transactions as they occur. Our app provides in-depth analysis to help you stay ahead of the curve.

FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about our Ethereum transaction analysis app
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Our app provides real-time analysis of new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain. It monitors the network, decodes incoming transactions, and provides insights into transaction details like sender, receiver, value transferred, and smart contract interactions.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_2: How quickly are new transactions analyzed?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: New transactions are analyzed within seconds of being included in a new block on the Ethereum network. Our systems are designed for low-latency ingestion and processing of blockchain data.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: Key details provided include the sender and receiver addresses, ETH value transferred, gas used, any ERC-20 token transfers, and decoded input data for smart contract function calls.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: Can I get alerts for certain transaction types?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, you can set up customized alerts to notify you whenever transactions matching specific criteria occur, such as high-value transfers or interactions with certain smart contracts.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: How can I access the app and data?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: The app provides both a web dashboard for easy viewing of recent transactions as well as APIs to stream transaction data into your own systems or applications in real-time.
